<plot>The film follows two friends who reunite after ten years. Kalani has stayed on Maui and is caught up in his successful fast-paced construction business, while Nalu, who is returning to rediscover the beauty of the island, adjusts to the changes of "progress". Kalani's constant fighting with his wife Kim, distant relationship with his son Conan, stress at his job, a lingering toothache and a near death experience brings the protagonist to a breaking point resulting in radical changes for Kalani and those around him. With unassuming help from Nalu, the family learns to better appreciate life on the island. In the end it is all about Ohana (family) and Aloha (love and respect). The film highlights the ethnic diversity of Maui and portrays the many different cultures living on the Hawaiian islands. The meanings of "local" and "born and raised" are discussed through different opinions and perspectives, along with the historical and cultural roots of the word "Haole". The Ice epidemic is presented in a subtle way, showing how a person addicted to methamphetamine can interact with family and society without being detected.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?229355</url></doc>
